#. type: Title #
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Opening files directly in PhpStorm"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "Yii error pages can show links that open stack trace files in PhpStorm at the failing line. This is useful in local development when the error page runs in a browser and the project is open in the IDE."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Check Toolbox links"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"PhpStorm supports Toolbox URLs that use the `jetbrains://` protocol. To get the `project` value and path format,\n"
"right-click a project file in the Project tool window and select **Copy Path/Reference** > **Toolbox URL**.\n"
"If the copied URL has `origin`, keep the `origin` parameter and its value in your links.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "On Linux, check that Toolbox registered the protocol handler:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (shell)
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "xdg-mime query default x-scheme-handler/jetbrains\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "The command should print a Toolbox or JetBrains daemon desktop file, for example `jetbrainsd.desktop`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "PhpStorm should be running with the project open when you click stack trace links."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Configuring the Mailer"
msgid "Configure error trace links"
msgstr "配置邮件发送器"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "The Yii application template configures `Yiisoft\\ErrorHandler\\Renderer\\HtmlRenderer` in `config/common/di/error-handler.php`. It reads a `traceLink` parameter and uses it for stack trace file links."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Add the following configuration to `config/common/params.php`:"
msgid "Add the parameter to `config/common/params.php`:"
msgstr "将以下配置添加到 `config/common/params.php`："

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<?php\n"
"\n"
"declare(strict_types=1);\n"
"\n"
"return [\n"
"    'traceLink' => 'jetbrains://phpstorm/navigate/reference?project=my-app&path={file}:{line}',\n"
"    // Other parameters.\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "Replace `my-app` with the `project` value from the Toolbox URL. If the Toolbox URL uses `origin`, keep `origin` in the link template and use its value."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "After that, open a debug error page and click a file link in the stack trace."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Map Docker paths to host paths"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "When the application runs in Docker, stack traces usually contain container paths such as `/app/src/...`.  PhpStorm needs the matching host path."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "Set `APP_HOST_PATH` in `docker/dev/override.env` to the project path on the host machine. Set `APP_IDE_PROJECT` to the `project` value from a Toolbox URL. If the URL uses `origin`, store the `origin` value instead and use `origin` in the final URL template:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (dotenv)
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"APP_HOST_PATH=/home/user/projects/my-app\n"
"APP_IDE_PROJECT=my-app\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "`docker/dev/override.env` is for developer-specific settings and shouldn't be committed. See [Override env files](../guide/tutorial/docker.md#override-env-files) for details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "In the application parameters, expose these environment values as `$params['app']['hostPath']` and `$params['app']['ideProject']`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "With the default application template, `/app/src/Web/HomePage/Action.php` will be linked as `/home/user/projects/my-app/src/Web/HomePage/Action.php`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure `HtmlRenderer` manually"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "If your application doesn't have the template's `error-handler.php` configuration, configure `HtmlRenderer` directly:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<?php\n"
"\n"
"declare(strict_types=1);\n"
"\n"
"use Yiisoft\\ErrorHandler\\Renderer\\HtmlRenderer;\n"
"\n"
"return [\n"
"    HtmlRenderer::class => [\n"
"        '__construct()' => [\n"
"            'traceLink' => 'jetbrains://phpstorm/navigate/reference?project=my-app&path={file}:{line}',\n"
"        ],\n"
"    ],\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
msgid "For Docker, use a closure to map the container path to the host path:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/cookbook/opening-files-in-phpstorm.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<?php\n"
"\n"
"declare(strict_types=1);\n"
"\n"
"/** @var array $params */\n"
"\n"
"use Yiisoft\\ErrorHandler\\Renderer\\HtmlRenderer;\n"
"\n"
"$hostPath = rtrim($params['app']['hostPath'], '/') . '/';\n"
"$project = $params['app']['ideProject'];\n"
"\n"
"return [\n"
"    HtmlRenderer::class => [\n"
"        '__construct()' => [\n"
"            'traceLink' => static function (string $file, ?int $line) use ($hostPath, $project): string {\n"
"                $file = preg_replace('~^/app/~', $hostPath, $file);\n"
"                $path = $line === null ? $file : $file . ':' . $line;\n"
"\n"
"                return str_replace(\n"
"                    ['{project}', '{path}'],\n"
"                    [$project, $path],\n"
"                    'jetbrains://phpstorm/navigate/reference?project={project}&path={path}',\n"
"                );\n"
"            },\n"
"        ],\n"
"    ],\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""
